      <block class="full_text">
        <p>ELIZABETH TAYLOR has one, and so do PRISCILLA PRESLEY and JULIO IGLESIAS . And now, so does GABRIELA SABATINI .</p>
        <p>The defending United States Open tennis champion is uncorking a "fragrance" (they don't call it "perfume" these days) called, fittingly, "Gabriela Sabatini."</p>
        <p>Records are skimpy in this area. But ANNETTE GREEN of the Fragrance Foundation says the only other athlete she knows that has had a fragrance named for him is MUHAMMAD ALI . "It's called 'Ali,' but I've never seen it on the shelves," she said.</p>
        <p>Oh, yes, there is one other sports-related scent on the market, says Green: It is called, simply, "Wimbledon."</p>
        <p>Now, if they could come up with, say, "Ebbets Field" (a hint of mustard, perhaps?) then it would reach the mainstream sports fan.  SIDELINES: EAU DE FLUSHING</p>
      </block>
